Character.isDigit(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a digit.
Character.isLetter(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a letter.
Character.isLetterOrDigit(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a letter or a digit.
Character.isWhitespace(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a whitespace character.
Character.isUpperCase(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is an uppercase letter.
Character.isLowerCase(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a lowercase letter.
Character.toUpperCase(char ch)

Converts the specified character to its uppercase form.
Character.toLowerCase(char ch)

Converts the specified character to its lowercase form.
Character.isDefined(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is defined in Unicode.
Character.isSurrogate(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a Unicode surrogate code unit.
Character.isTitleCase(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a titlecase character.
Character.getType(char ch)

Returns a value indicating a character's general category.
Character.isJavaIdentifierStart(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a valid start character for a Java identifier.
Character.isJavaIdentifierPart(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a valid part of a Java identifier.
Character.isUnicodeIdentifierStart(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a valid start character for a Unicode identifier.
Character.isUnicodeIdentifierPart(char ch)

Checks if the specified character is a valid part of a Unicode identifier.
Character.isIdentifierIgnorable(char ch)

Determines if the specified character should be regarded as an ignorable character in a Java identifier or a Unicode identifier.
Character.digit(char ch, int radix)

Converts the character (Unicode) to a digit in the specified radix.
Character.forDigit(int digit, int radix)

Returns the character representation of the specified digit in the specified radix.
Character.codePointAt(CharSequence seq, int index)

Returns the code point at the specified index of the specified CharSequence.
Character.codePointBefore(CharSequence seq, int index)

Returns the code point preceding the specified index of the specified CharSequence.
Character.codePointCount(CharSequence seq, int beginIndex, int endIndex)

Returns the number of Unicode code points in the text range of the specified CharSequence.
Character.toChars(int codePoint)

